Which step(s) should you take to establish rapport with clients?
A. Allow the sales team to call your client to offer new products and services
B. Let them know they should only call you; you will not call them
C. Stay engaged by holding regular meetings
D. Show your client what the competitors are doing
Answer: C
What are two different ways to maintain a strong and productive customer relationship?
(Choose two)
A. Do not try to sell other products or services
B. Schedule semiannual meetings only
C. Give clients some space; call them only if they need you
D. Review usage reports with clients
E. Meet regularly depending on client needs
Answer: D,E
Which two are characteristics of a successful implementation? (Choose two.)
A. Configuration
B. Design
C. Assimilation
D. Submitting branding requests
E. Preparation
Answer: C,E

Which business complexity example is best described as a consumerization trend?
A. Following workers that work outside of business hours
B. Managing tools and helping people find the correct content in a secure location when
needed
C. Employees bringing in new devices and applications into work
D. Resolving issues over distances
